      "id": "overview",
      "title": "Role Overview",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "Management Consulting interviews are among the most rigorous. You'll face case interviews testing structured thinking, fit interviews assessing cultural alignment, and often group exercises or presentations."
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**What interviewers assess:**\n\n- Structured problem-solving (case interviews)\n- Quantitative and analytical skills\n- Communication and executive presence\n- Leadership and teamwork\n- Cultural fit and motivation"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "format",
      "title": "Common Interview Format",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "content": {
            "text": "**Typical consulting interview loop:**\n\n- **First round** (2-3 interviews):\n  - Case interview + fit questions\n  - May include written case or math test\n\n- **Final round** (3-4 interviews):\n  - Partner/principal case interviews\n  - Deeper fit/behavioral discussions\n  - Sometimes group case or presentation"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "tip",
          "content": {
            "text": "Practice 50+ cases before interviews. Case performance improves dramatically with practiceâ€”there's no substitute for reps."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
